|><| 𝐓𝐞𝐫𝐧𝐚𝐫𝐲 𝐎𝐩𝐞𝐫𝐚𝐭𝐨𝐫 |><|
      >> It is condensed form of if-else statement which evaluates a condition.
      >> It execute the code based on evaluated conditions.
      >> It evaluates a boolean expression and returns true & false.

𝚂𝚢𝚗𝚝𝚊𝚡 ::--
     result = (condition) ? value1 : value2;

    > condition : A boolean expression.
    >   value1  : The value returned if the condition is true.
    >   value2  : The value returned if the condition is false.

𝙴𝚡𝚊𝚖𝚙𝚕𝚎  ::--

  class Main {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        int number = 10;

        // Using ternary operator
        String result = (number > 5) ? "true" : "false";

        System.out.println(result); // Output: Greater than 5
      }
   }
 
